  "text": "fixation, negative staining, and visualization by Transmission Electron Microscopy (TEM) [CITATION_1] . Regarding their biochemical composition, Exo are surrounded by a phospholipid membrane with high levels of cholesterol, sphingomyelin, and ceramide. Moreover, they are characterized by the presence of proteins involved in membrane transport and fusion, associated to the endosome formation, (such as Rab, GTPases, and Annexins), by components of the Endosomal Sorting Complexes Required for Transporter (ESCRTs) and by tetraspanins, including CD9, CD63, and CD81 [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] .",
